annotationA: 60S ribosomal protein L28; Structural constituent of ribosome. It is involved in the biological process described with: mitotic spindle elongation; translation; centrosome duplication; mitotic spindle organization; neurogenesis; Belongs to the eukaryotic ribosomal protein eL28 family
annotationB: Trifunctional purine biosynthetic protein adenosine-3; Phosphoribosylglycinamide formyltransferase activity; methyltransferase activity; ATP binding; metal ion binding; phosphoribosylamine-glycine ligase activity; phosphoribosylformylglycinamidine cyclo-ligase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: purine nucleobase biosynthetic process; 'de novo' IMP biosynthetic process; In the central section; belongs to the AIR synthase family
